 on Mu&#8217;awwidhatayn: Best two chapters for seeking refuge in Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 20, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn \u2018Abis al-Juhani reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said to him, \u201cO Ibn \u2018Abis, shall I not tell you about the best way to seek refuge for those who seek it?\u201d He said, \u201cOf course, O Messenger of Allah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThese two\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4003,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/two-surahs-refuge-falaq-nas\/","url_meta":{"origin":34322,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Refuge with Surat al-Falaq and al-Nas","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would seek refuge from jinn and the evil eye of man, until 'the two chapters of refuge' were revealed, al-Falaq and al-Nas. After they were revealed, he held to them and left everything else. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34807,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/25\/falaq-nas-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":34322,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Recite al-Falaq and al-Nas after prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 25, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Uqbah ibn \u2018Amir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, commanded me to recite the two chapters of refuge, al-Falaq and al-Nas, at the end of every prayer. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2903 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Ibn Hajar \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064f\u0642\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17444,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/01\/surah-falaq-nas-sleep\/","url_meta":{"origin":34322,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Reciting Surat al-Falaq and al-Nas before sleep","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 1, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: When the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would lie down for sleep, he would blow into his hands, recite the two chapters of refuge, al-Falaq and al-Nas, and he would wipe his hands over his body. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5960 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34320,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/07\/20\/surat-al-ikhlaas-jannah-obligatory\/","url_meta":{"origin":34322,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Surat al-Ikhlas makes Paradise obligatory","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 20, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: I met with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he heard a man reciting the verses, \u201cSay: He is Allah, the One, the Eternal Refuge,\u201d (112:1-2). The Prophet said, \u201cIt is necessary for him.\u201d I said, \u201cWhat is necessary?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cParadise.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/34322","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=34322"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/34322\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=34322"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=34322"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyh